The paper focuses on the design and implementation of a Multipath IP (MPIP) protocol for orchestrating multipath transmission at the network layer of end devices. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) as it deals with the design and implementation of a network protocol. The paper also discusses the performance of MPIP, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), architecture (cs.AR), information theory (cs.IT), and operating systems (cs.OS). However, since the main focus is on network protocols and performance, cs.NI is the most likely category, followed by the other categories in decreasing order of likelihood.
